00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:31.290
IAN NI-LEWIS: Hello and welcome
back to the Friday

00:01:31.290 --> 00:01:32.600
Games Review.

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:34.100
I am Ian Ni-Lewis.

00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:35.230
DAN GALPIN: And I'm
Dan Galpin.

00:01:35.230 --> 00:01:38.040
And we're going to be looking at
a bunch of Halloween games

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:42.860
as well as chatting, as we
always do, talking about the

00:01:42.860 --> 00:01:46.990
technology behind games and how
we can make more awesome

00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:48.980
games on Android.

00:01:48.980 --> 00:01:54.760
IAN NI-LEWIS: And, sad to say,
this is the final episode of

00:01:54.760 --> 00:01:57.090
the Friday Games Review.

00:01:57.090 --> 00:01:59.090
We've both moved on.

00:01:59.090 --> 00:02:02.060
[LAUGHING]

00:02:02.060 --> 00:02:03.300
DAN GALPIN: We've
both moved on.

00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:04.320
IAN NI-LEWIS: Right.

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:07.930
You know, at some point, you
gotta ask yourself, how much

00:02:07.930 --> 00:02:11.140
beer am I going to
drink for my job?

00:02:11.140 --> 00:02:13.370
And the answer is, a lot.

00:02:13.370 --> 00:02:14.380
And now--

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:17.350
DAN GALPIN: I think that part
will continue, though.

00:02:17.350 --> 00:02:18.380
IAN NI-LEWIS: Oh,
you never know.

00:02:18.380 --> 00:02:20.700
Anyway, so today we're
drinking, again,

00:02:20.700 --> 00:02:22.220
Rogue Dead Guy Ale.

00:02:22.220 --> 00:02:22.740
DAN GALPIN: Exactly.

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:24.770
IAN NI-LEWIS: Because it's
Halloweeny, and because this

00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:25.910
show is dead.

00:02:25.910 --> 00:02:28.270
Now we're not going off
the air permanently.

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:30.180
We're going to be back
at some point.

00:02:30.180 --> 00:02:34.300
I think Dan's going to be
headlining a new act, trying

00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:36.070
to get something together
with maybe Colt

00:02:36.070 --> 00:02:37.630
McAnlis or those guys.

00:02:37.630 --> 00:02:41.730
Basically, what's happened is
it used to be all about

00:02:41.730 --> 00:02:42.630
Android with us.

00:02:42.630 --> 00:02:48.435
And now, Dan's sort of taken on
a role that is more global,

00:02:48.435 --> 00:02:51.620
a little bit more
cross-Google.

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:54.880
And I think that as soon as he's
ready to talk about that,

00:02:54.880 --> 00:02:57.620
I think he's going to come back
with some cool stuff.

00:02:57.620 --> 00:02:59.070
DAN GALPIN: Basically, it means
that I could spend a lot

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:01.700
of time with Colt and with Todd
Kerpelman and a bunch of

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:03.640
other people here, and that's
going to be great.

00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:05.290
And I'm trying to encourage
them to wear

00:03:05.290 --> 00:03:07.020
crazy hats as well.

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:07.580
So we'll see.

00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:09.210
Hopefully we'll see more crazy
hats in the future.

00:03:09.210 --> 00:03:13.040
By the way, this hat is not just
a crazy hat with hair,

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:17.010
which is partially in honor of
the amazing picture that was

00:03:17.010 --> 00:03:21.570
put together by Daniel
Pham in response to

00:03:21.570 --> 00:03:23.600
our fauxhawk comments--

00:03:23.600 --> 00:03:24.720
IAN NI-LEWIS: That's right.

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:24.950
Last week, we--

00:03:24.950 --> 00:03:26.080
DAN GALPIN: Comments
from last week.

00:03:26.080 --> 00:03:28.310
IAN NI-LEWIS: We intimated that
perhaps Daniel Pham was

