anyway, he was kind enough
to put together this.

00:03:45.115 --> 00:03:46.365
Dan went--

00:04:08.440 --> 00:04:10.100
DAN GALPIN: And it's something
like that.

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:12.620
So speaking of stronger, so the
hat that I'm wearing, if

00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:16.070
you can't tell, is actually a
San Francisco Giants hat.

00:04:16.070 --> 00:04:19.060
And no, I did not get to go and
attend the World Series.

00:04:19.060 --> 00:04:22.400
But I did stand outside of the
ballpark yesterday and watch

00:04:22.400 --> 00:04:23.320
the end of the game.

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:26.190
And it was kind of epic
just being there with

00:04:26.190 --> 00:04:27.370
the cheering fans.

00:04:27.370 --> 00:04:28.440
IAN NI-LEWIS: You watched
the end of the

00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:30.000
game outside the ballpark?

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.750
DAN GALPIN: On televisions
literally in the plaza in

00:04:32.750 --> 00:04:33.700
front of the ballpark.

00:04:33.700 --> 00:04:37.060
And it was great because we had
about a 10-second delay.

00:04:37.060 --> 00:04:39.670
So when anything would happen in
the game that was awesome,

00:04:39.670 --> 00:04:41.160
we'd hear the cheers
from them.

00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:43.510
And then 10 seconds later, you'd
hear the cheers from us

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:47.580
all waiting outside in the less
than cheap standing area.

00:04:47.580 --> 00:04:50.390
But it was awesome and epic, and
it was exciting to see the

00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:52.320
Giants go up 2-0, for
all those who are

00:04:52.320 --> 00:04:55.360
Giants fans out there.

00:04:55.360 --> 00:04:59.240
And yeah, so this hat is
actually a SF Giants hat.

00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:03.910
But it also just kind of fits
with the fauxhawk theme we had

00:05:03.910 --> 00:05:05.070
from last week.

00:05:05.070 --> 00:05:07.060
IAN NI-LEWIS: You know, the
thing about your fauxhawk is,

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:08.970
it really didn't turn
into a fauxhawk.

00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:10.250
I mean, mine was--

00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:11.810
I don't even know
what mine was.

00:05:11.810 --> 00:05:13.060
I think it was a--

00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:23.400
so epic, it makes me want to put
you on the cover of a '70s

00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:24.775
funk album.

00:05:24.775 --> 00:05:25.620
It's Doug Henning.

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:31.360
It's like, you are the '70s
magician, the groovy magician

00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:33.060
of Android.

00:05:33.060 --> 00:05:33.870
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, something
like that.

00:05:33.870 --> 00:05:35.130
IAN NI-LEWIS: Bringing
mullets back.

00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:37.695
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, absolutely.

00:05:37.695 --> 00:05:39.910
IAN NI-LEWIS: Can we see that
with the motion, Dan?

00:05:39.910 --> 00:05:41.040
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, let's--

00:05:41.040 --> 00:05:42.470
you mean this with the motion?

00:05:42.470 --> 00:05:43.180
DANIEL PHAM: Yeah, do
you want to see--

00:05:43.180 --> 00:05:44.170
DAN GALPIN: Or do you want
me to do the motion?

00:05:44.170 --> 00:05:44.660
Oh, I see.

00:05:44.660 --> 00:05:46.590
Yeah, absolutely, with
the work that Ian has

00:05:46.590 --> 00:05:47.560
put together to make--

00:05:47.560 --> 00:05:48.525
IAN NI-LEWIS: Right.

00:05:48.525 --> 00:05:49.930
DAN GALPIN: --to make
me more epic.

00:05:56.570 --> 00:05:58.700
I don't think I could look
at myself that often.

00:05:58.700 --> 00:06:00.980
But I'll mention it
to my girlfriend.

00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:02.945
She might like it.

00:06:02.945 --> 00:06:04.315
IAN NI-LEWIS: I wasn't
talking to you.

00:06:04.315 --> 00:06:04.680
DAN GALPIN: Oh.

00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:06.470
IAN NI-LEWIS: I was talking
to everyone out there in

00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:08.970
Internet-land.

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:10.820
DAN GALPIN: So, we do--

