00:06:26.420 --> 00:06:28.180
DAN GALPIN: Probably,
probably.

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:28.900
Yeah.

00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:30.580
Yeah, you should have
nominated some

00:06:30.580 --> 00:06:32.220
games, Ian's wife.

00:06:32.220 --> 00:06:37.200
But in all fairness, so
we are going to cover

00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:37.980
some Halloween games.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:39.920
There was one game that's
sort of borderline.

00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:43.230
I also wanted to mention that
"Greedy Spiders" actually went

00:06:43.230 --> 00:06:46.170
and got updated based
upon the comments we

00:06:46.170 --> 00:06:47.000
made from last week.

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:47.640
IAN NI-LEWIS: Rock on.

00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:49.740
DAN GALPIN: So thanks,
guys, for doing that.

00:06:49.740 --> 00:06:52.620
I've definitely let the
Google Play team know.

00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:55.770
And as soon as they're out from
under the epic burden

00:06:55.770 --> 00:06:59.200
they've been under in the last
week or so, hopefully we'll

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:01.510
see something happen with that
because it's a great game.

00:07:01.510 --> 00:07:06.390
IAN NI-LEWIS: Yeah, it's worth
mentioning, too, the amazing

00:07:06.390 --> 00:07:08.200
burden that these people
put themselves under

00:07:08.200 --> 00:07:09.170
every holiday season.

00:07:09.170 --> 00:07:12.850
It's really, really difficult
to be a Google Play

00:07:12.850 --> 00:07:17.070
merchandising guy in
any holiday season.

00:07:17.070 --> 00:07:21.400
So remember to get those updates
up two, three weeks

00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:24.030
beforehand if you want
to be considered for

00:07:24.030 --> 00:07:25.990
featuring at a holiday.

00:07:25.990 --> 00:07:27.890
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, it's
totally brutal.

00:07:27.890 --> 00:07:28.800
It kind of works, though.

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.840
Because as far as I can tell in
this country, Christmas is

00:07:31.840 --> 00:07:32.960
now beginning in August.

00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:36.230
That was when I first saw the
Christmas merchandise showing

00:07:36.230 --> 00:07:38.055
up in stores, was in August
of this year.

00:07:38.055 --> 00:07:38.320
IAN NI-LEWIS: What?

00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:39.000
DAN GALPIN: I know

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:39.580
IAN NI-LEWIS: What store
had Christmas

00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:40.290
merchandise in August?

00:07:40.290 --> 00:07:41.690
DAN GALPIN: Costco, actually,
was like--

00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:42.690
I was totally amazed.

00:07:42.690 --> 00:07:43.520
IAN NI-LEWIS: Oh.

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:44.390
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, I know.

00:07:44.390 --> 00:07:46.040
IAN NI-LEWIS: I guess they
have to truck it in.

00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:50.980
DAN GALPIN: So in any case,
given that, having something

00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:53.030
up two or three weeks before
the holiday actually is a

00:07:53.030 --> 00:07:54.310
really good idea.

00:07:54.310 --> 00:07:57.570
If you are a game team, and you
are just trucking to get

00:07:57.570 --> 00:08:01.560
something done the day before
the holiday, and then you want

00:08:01.560 --> 00:08:04.410
the team to have time to look
at it, that's probably not

00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:06.530
going to happen, especially when
the team is also trying

00:08:06.530 --> 00:08:08.930
to prepare for an event that's
going to happen on Monday.

00:08:08.930 --> 00:08:10.390
So--

00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:12.950
and not that we can talk about
what that event will be, other

00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:15.320
than the playground is open.

00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:17.410
Isn't that what they
said about it?

00:08:17.410 --> 00:08:17.971
IAN NI-LEWIS: Is that really
what we said? "The

00:08:17.971 --> 00:08:18.230
playground is open"?

00:08:18.230 --> 00:08:19.220
DAN GALPIN: I think that's
what we said,

00:08:19.220 --> 00:08:20.140
something like that.

00:08:20.140 --> 00:08:21.850
IAN NI-LEWIS: Wow,
how exciting.

00:08:21.850 --> 00:08:23.570
DAN GALPIN: I know, I know.

00:08:23.570 --> 00:08:25.820
Yeah, I'm looking forward to
that event actually happening

00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:29.660
so that life can go back
to normal, right?

00:08:29.660 --> 00:08:29.920
Yeah?

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:31.160
IAN NI-LEWIS: I hope so.

00:08:31.160 --> 00:08:32.350
DAN GALPIN: I hope so.

00:08:32.350 --> 00:08:34.830
Of course, then, with this
hair, who knows?

00:08:34.830 --> 00:08:36.730
So I did look at a bunch
of games this week.

00:08:36.730 --> 00:08:41.929
The first one is "Gun Zombie
Halloween." Now, honestly, if

00:08:41.929 --> 00:08:47.410
"Gun Zombie" by itself was not
Halloweeny enough, we have the

00:08:47.410 --> 00:08:49.840
Gun Zombie Halloween edition.

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:50.320
IAN NI-LEWIS: Whoa.

00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:51.240
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, exactly.

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:52.800
So just to show you--

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:54.835
IAN NI-LEWIS: So I think what
we want to do today is rate

00:08:54.835 --> 00:08:59.520
games on A, how good they are
and B, how shamelessly they

00:08:59.520 --> 00:09:01.950
chiseled in some sort
of Halloween theme--

00:09:01.950 --> 00:09:02.340
DAN GALPIN: Yes.

00:09:02.340 --> 00:09:03.830
IAN NI-LEWIS: Whether or
not it fit, right?

00:09:03.830 --> 00:09:04.060
DAN GALPIN: Yeah.

00:09:04.060 --> 00:09:06.780
And actually, most of the ones
I picked today really were

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:08.560
games that should have had
a Halloween theme.

00:09:08.560 --> 00:09:10.160
So I didn't look out
for the ones that

00:09:10.160 --> 00:09:10.830
were shameless, like--

00:09:10.830 --> 00:09:11.340
IAN NI-LEWIS: Did you get
"Clouds and Sheep"?

00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:13.010
DAN GALPIN: I did not put
"Clouds and Sheep" Halloween

00:09:13.010 --> 00:09:13.460
edition up there.

00:09:13.460 --> 00:09:15.440
IAN NI-LEWIS: But shoutout to
our buddies at HandyGames.

00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:16.910
DAN GALPIN: Dudes, awesome
job with that one.

00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:19.680
So this one here, your job is
to shoot things as they walk

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:22.400
towards you, thus eliminating
them from having to actually

00:09:22.400 --> 00:09:24.670
have a view of anything
from the side,

00:09:24.670 --> 00:09:27.790
which is kind of epic.

00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:30.750
